  "prompt": "Why don't people answer me on Quora?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why people might not be answering your questions on Quora:\n\n1. **Question Clarity**: Make sure your question is clear and concise. If it's difficult to understand, people might skip over it.\n\n2. **Subject Matter**: If your question is about a very niche or uncommon topic, there may not be many people who are knowledgeable enough to answer.\n\n3. **Question Quality**: High-quality questions that provoke thoughtful answers are more likely to get responses. Ensure your question is interesting and well-formulated.\n\n4. **Activity Levels**: Sometimes, the community or topic you are asking about might just be less active, leading to fewer responses.\n\n5. **Timing**: The time at which you post your question could affect visibility. Posting at peak times might increase the likelihood of getting answers.\n\n6. **Engagement**: Engaging with the community by answering other questions and upvoting answers can increase your visibility, leading to more responses to your own questions.\n\n7. **Profile Visibility**: Make sure your profile is complete and engaging. A well-rounded profile can encourage others to interact with you.\n\n8. **Promotion**: Occasionally, it helps to share your question on other social media platforms or ask specific experts to help shed light on your query.\n\nIf you've considered these factors and are still not getting responses, try revising your question or engaging more with the community to increase your chances of receiving answers.",
